text: University of Twente (Dutch: Universiteit Twente), shortened to UT, is a technical public university in Enschede, a city in the province of Overijssel, the Netherlands. It borders the municipality of Hengelo. The University of Twente was established in 1961. It was called Technical College of Twente (Dutch: Technische Hogeschool Twente) until 1986. It has about 10,000 students. Its focus is on technology and social sciences. == Other websites == * Category:Enschede Twente Category:1960s establishments in the Netherlands Category:1961 establishments in Europe
